--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages bsd_grep.

The BSD versions of commonly used grep utilities. Grep searches through textual
input for lines which contain a match to a specified pattern and then prints
the matching lines.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: bsd_grep
       bsd_grep_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: bsd_grep
       bsd_grep_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: bsd_grep
       bsd_grep_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  bsd_grep_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

